Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.00,0:00:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,By 14,000 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.00,0:00:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the Ice Age was winding down.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.00,0:00:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As the ice melted, oceans rose, and coastlines changed,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.00,0:00:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,some environmental barriers between populations vanished.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.00,0:00:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,While elsewhere, new ones appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.00,0:00:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Temperatures and rainfall increased dramatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.00,0:00:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And some areas became so rich in plants and animals,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.00,0:00:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that people no longer had to travel in search of food.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.00,0:01:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, people settled into more permanent villages based on foraging.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.00,0:01:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,By planting the seeds from wild grains near their homes,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.00,0:01:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,they could supplement their food supplies, and stay in the same spot year round.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.00,0:01:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps as they became more sedentary,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.00,0:01:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they had more opportunities for other, ahem, pursuits.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.00,0:01:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, populations grew
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.00,0:01:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and pretty soon, growing families in these villages became less suited to the nomadic lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.00,0:01:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In some places, during droughts or harsh winters,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.00,0:01:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,local wild plants and animals could no longer support everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.00,0:01:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Independently and all over the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.00,0:01:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,people began making the same discovery,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.00,0:02:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,which would change human societies and the natural environment forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.00,0:02:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They developed
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.00,0:02:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,AGRICULTURE!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.00,0:02:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not an obvious choice,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.00,0:02:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,hunter-gatherers can provide
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.00,0:02:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,food for their families, by working only a few days a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.60,0:02:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Farming, on the other hand, is hard work, and a full-time job.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.00,0:02:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But farming provided more food to feed larger populations consistently
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.00,0:02:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Villages began relying more and more on their gardens.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.00,0:02:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As mutant varieties of wild grains occured,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.00,0:02:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,these early agriculturists
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.00,0:02:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,chose the crops with larger seeds
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.00,0:02:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and grain ears that were easier to gather.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.00,0:03:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,People also domesticated docile, local animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.00,0:03:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Villages grew, especially in areas with fertile soil, and became cities.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.00,0:03:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And settled people became more detached from the natural world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.00,0:03:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,By 6,000 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.00,0:03:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in Mesopotamia, there were cities
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.00,0:03:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with wealth, power, and a new social order.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.00,0:03:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoever controlled grain supplies wielded power.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.00,0:03:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And some people no longer had to find
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.00,0:03:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or produce their own food,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.00,0:03:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but rather exchange their services for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.00,0:03:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Agricultural societies
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.00,0:04:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,soon became the dominant way of life for people throughout the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.00,0:04:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,World populations exploded,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.00,0:04:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,creating more laborers to produce more crops,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.00,0:04:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to feed more mouths,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.00,0:04:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,more land had to be cleared for farming.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.00,0:04:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes, whole towns relocated
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.00,0:04:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when soils couldn't sustain repeated cultivation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.00,0:04:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And each year, people took their livestock
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.00,0:04:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,farther and farther afield to graze.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.00,0:04:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Groups who had been separated for thousands of years came in contact
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.00,0:04:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as they traveled in search of land, labor, and trade goods.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.00,0:04:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,New means of transportation brought distant cultures in contact.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.00,0:05:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,New families produced from these contacts blurred genetic distinctions
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.00,0:05:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,within continents,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.00,0:05:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and all around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.00,0:05:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Migrating farmers encountered hunter-gatherers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.00,0:05:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In sub-Saharan Africa, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.00,0:05:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,farmers spread east and south from present-day Cameroon around 5,000 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.00,0:05:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Along the way, they met and absorbed
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.00,0:05:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,many of the people whose ancestors had been living there for thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.00,0:05:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Some hunter-gatherers who lived next to farming communities took up farming themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.00,0:05:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But others followed game to areas unsuited to agriculture.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.00,0:05:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,By 1,500 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.00,0:06:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,agriculture dominated most of sub-Saharan Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.00,0:06:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Calahari Desert, too harsh for farming, remained a home of hunter-gatherers,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.00,0:06:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,who kept not only much of their lifestyle, but also their unique click languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.00,0:06:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In most places throughout the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.00,0:06:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,however, agriculture triumphed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.00,0:06:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As the new farmers on each continent
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.00,0:06:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,expanded and absorbed other hunter-gatherer groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.00,0:06:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Genetic differences within continents began disappearing,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.00,0:06:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,setting the stage for the most recent chapter in our human story.
